        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 17 at 6:39PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 639 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles east of Ballantine moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, half inch size hail, and
torrential rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pompeys Pillar.

This statement does not include the city of Billings.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
